# Alice Blog — Development Guidelines

Auto-generated from feature plans. Last updated: 2026-03-05

## Active Technologies

- TypeScript 5 (strict) + Next.js 16 App Router + React 19 (001-blog-foundation)
- Tailwind CSS v4 (CSS @theme tokens, no tailwind.config) (001-blog-foundation)
- Prisma 6 + PostgreSQL 16 — DAL-only access (001-blog-foundation)
- Zod 3 — validation on all Server Action inputs (001-blog-foundation)

## Project Structure

```text
src/
├── app/                     # Routes & layouts (Server Components by default)
├── actions/                 # Server Actions (mutations only)
├── data-access/             # DAL — "use cache" + cacheTag (reads only)
├── components/
│   ├── ui/                  # Atomic design-system primitives
│   └── blog/                # Feature organisms
└── lib/
    ├── prisma.ts            # Singleton Prisma client
    ├── types.ts             # ActionResult<T> shared types
    └── schemas/             # Zod schemas per entity
prisma/
├── schema.prisma
└── seed.ts
```

## Commands

```bash
pnpm dev            # Start dev server
pnpm typecheck      # tsc --noEmit
pnpm lint           # ESLint
pnpm build          # Production build
pnpm prisma migrate dev   # Run migrations
pnpm prisma db seed       # Seed database
```

## Code Style

- **Components**: `export function ComponentName()` — named export, PascalCase
- **Utilities/hooks**: `export const fn = () => {}` — arrow function
- **File names**: kebab-case matching the exported symbol
- **Server Actions**: prefixed with verb (`createComment`, `toggleLike`)
- **DAL functions**: prefixed with `get`/`query` (`getPostBySlug`)
- **Imports order**: external → internal (`@/`) → relative
- **No `any`** — use `unknown` and narrow explicitly
- **No `useEffect`** for data fetching — use Server Components or DAL

## Cache Convention

- DAL functions MUST use `"use cache"` + `cacheTag("<entity>:<id>")`
- Tags: `post:<slug>`, `comments:<postId>`, `likes:<postId>`, `posts:list`
- Mutations MUST call `revalidateTag()` after successful write

